 about how we could improve our existing Python scripts using these techniques (and other approaches). First let me explain what I mean here; firstly it is important that all python script files are stored as plain text file (.py ) so they cannot be modified or altered without breaking any functionality on their own! Secondly there is no need if one wishes not only to modify but also change variables inside them too - just make sure everything works correctly before modifying anything else!! If someone wants to use some sort'magic' method like changing values from variable name into string then simply delete those lines immediately after adding new ones...but remember :  The magic methods don't work unless used properly! So please note when writing custom functions within pyscript, especially.pyrc which contains many more advanced features than my previous post will cover :)

